<html><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="css/tips.css"></head><body><p><b>Edit multiple lines at the same time</b></p><p>Press <span class="shortcut">&shortcut:EditorToggleColumnMode;</span> to toggle the <span class="control">column selection</span> mode on. In this mode, you can make the same change on multiple lines. For example, it's useful if you need to render some text as a list and wrap several lines in the same tag. Use the same shortcut to toggle the mode off.</p><p class="image"><img src="images/ps_tips-multiselection_column.png" alt="Column selection mode" style="border: 1px solid #55555;" /></p></body></html>